President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. These appointments include Major General Marcelite Harris, USAF (Ret) and Lieutenant General Arlen D. Jameson, USAF (Ret) as members of the Board of Visitors to the United States Air Force Academy, Elizabeth Young McNally as a member of the Board of Visitors to the United States Military Academy, Patrick J. Murphy as a member of the Board of Visitors to the United States Military Academy, and Sally Susman as a member of the Library of Congress Trust Fund Board. President Obama commended these individuals for their knowledge and dedication throughout their careers and expressed gratitude for their willingness to take on these important roles. The appointed individuals have impressive backgrounds and accomplishments in various fields, such as military service, corporate affairs, and government relations.